For this task, I will choose Proposal 1 - Create a Portfolio page. Here is a simplified example of how this could be done:



<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My Portfolio</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="portfolio">
        <img src="my-photo.jpg" alt="My Photo" class="portfolio-image">
        <h1 class="portfolio-title">My Portfolio</h1>
        <h2 class="portfolio-subtitle">Web Developer</h2>
        <p class="portfolio-text">Hello, my name is Amel and I am developing instoxx...</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>



body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    background-color: #f0f0f0;
}

.portfolio {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 20px;
}

.portfolio-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
}

.portfolio-title {
    color: #333;
    text-align: center;
}

.portfolio-subtitle {
    color: #777;
    text-align: center;
}

.portfolio-text {
    color: #333;
    text-align: justify;
}
This is a very basic portfolio page with a photo of yourself, a title (h1 tag), a subtitle (h2 tag), and a text description (p tag). The CSS file styles.css is linked in the head of the HTML document, and this file contains all the styles that make the webpage look better. 
